# wpe-targets — maps each WP Engine git remote to its SSH gateway, so the
# pre-push hook can version-check the deploy against the live server.
#
# One line per environment (whitespace-separated):
#
#   <remote-url-substring>   <ssh-gateway-host>                         <install-name>
#
# The substring just has to uniquely match the remote URL. Example:
#
#   production/myprod    myprod@myprod.ssh.wpengine.net      myprod
#   production/mystage   mystage@mystage.ssh.wpengine.net    mystage
#
# Find your install names + gateway hosts:
#   ssh -T git@git.wpengine.com          (lists installs your key can reach)
#   WP Engine portal → each environment's Overview (SSH gateway string)
#
# Until you add a line here, the pre-push version-drift check is skipped
# (the file-type check still runs). This file is yours — it is not overwritten.
